  "prompt": "What Pok\u00e9mon hatches from Eggs in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "The Pok\u00e9mon that can hatch from Eggs in Pok\u00e9mon GO change periodically with events and updates. However, here's a general overview of how Egg hatching works and what influences the Pok\u00e9mon you might get:\n\n**Egg Types:**\n\n*   **2 km Eggs:** Generally hatch common Pok\u00e9mon.\n*   **5 km Eggs:** Hatch somewhat less common Pok\u00e9mon.\n*   **7 km Eggs:** Usually hatch Alolan or Galarian forms of Pok\u00e9mon (or regional exclusive Pok\u00e9mon during some events). These are obtained from opening Gifts from friends.\n*   **10 km Eggs:** Hatch rarer Pok\u00e9mon.\n*   **12 km Eggs (Strange Eggs):** Hatch Dark- and Poison-type Pok\u00e9mon or Pok\u00e9mon that evolve into Dark or Poison types. Obtained by defeating Team GO Rocket Leaders.\n*   **Adventure Sync Eggs (5 km and 10 km):** You receive these as rewards for walking a certain distance during the Adventure Sync week. These usually have a special pool of Pok\u00e9mon that can hatch from them.\n\n**Important Factors Influencing Hatches:**\n\n*   **Event Bonuses:** During events, the pool of Pok\u00e9mon that can hatch from Eggs changes. Certain Pok\u00e9mon may become more common or exclusive to certain Egg types during specific events.\n*   **Egg Acquisition Date:** The Pok\u00e9mon inside an Egg is determined at the moment you receive the Egg from a Pok\u00e9Stop, Gym, or Adventure Sync reward. This means that even if the hatch pool changes later, the Pok\u00e9mon in the Egg you already have is already set.\n*   **Rarity Tiers:** Within each Egg type, Pok\u00e9mon are categorized into rarity tiers (Common, Uncommon, Rare, Very Rare). Rarer Pok\u00e9mon are, well, rarer to hatch.\n*   **Regional Exclusives:** Some regional exclusive Pok\u00e9mon can hatch from 7 km Eggs during specific events.\n\n**Where to Find Current Hatch Lists:**\n\n*   **Leek Duck:** This website is reliable and usually has updated hatch lists.\n*   **Serebii.net:** A comprehensive Pok\u00e9mon resource that usually keeps track of Egg hatches.\n*   **Pok\u00e9mon GO News Websites/Blogs:** Many Pok\u00e9mon GO news sites will publish articles when Egg pools change.\n*   **In-Game News:** Keep an eye on the in-game News section for announcements about Egg-related events.\n\n**Tips for Hatching:**\n\n*   **Incubators:** Use Incubators to hatch Eggs. The more incubators you use at once, the faster you can hatch Eggs.\n*   **Super Incubators:** These incubators hatch Eggs faster than regular Incubators. They're usually available in the in-game shop.\n*   **Walk Regularly:** The more you walk, the more Eggs you can hatch.\n*   **Pay Attention to Events:** Take advantage of events that offer bonuses for hatching Eggs.\n\nGood luck with your Egg hatching!",
